The paper discusses the application of persistent homology, a method from computational algebraic topology, to analyze data related to the Brexit referendum. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of computer science that deals with data analysis and visualization, such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of cs.SD (Software Development) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as these fields often involve the use of data analysis techniques.
